<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/22817184-christopher-febles"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1639773335i/22817184._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/22817184-christopher-febles">Christopher Febles</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Hi - far be it from me to judge, but Leviathan and Moon Palace are just wonderful. Thought-provoking, gripping, detailed, bleak and hopeful. Love it w<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Hi - far be it from me to judge, but Leviathan and Moon Palace are just wonderful. Thought-provoking, gripping, detailed, bleak and hopeful. Love it when he does first-person narration; you are privy to all the character's thoughts, anxieties, faults, hopes, desires. Also one of my favorites, though off the beaten path, a little wild in its structure and painfully long, is the 780-page long "4321." That was an odyssey but well worth the trip. And all his books are a welcome to Brooklyn.<br />Enjoy!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
