<div id="review_1713350816" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1713350816" />
    <a title="Paria:D" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57402378-paria-d"><img alt="Paria:D" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467777461p2/57402378.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1713350816?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paria:D" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paria:D" href="/user/show/57402378-paria-d">Paria:D</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57402378-paria-d?shelf=american">american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57402378-paria-d?shelf=novel">novel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57402378-paria-d?shelf=21-century">21-century</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1713350816" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12088657711377576553">Usually, Im not used to experience reading a book without any previous suggestion. I often choose them with regard to their reputation; but that day, I was too tired of walking along the streets, performing my university chores till 1 PM. I wonder how a bookstore just appeared in front of me and I was attracted to its yard.picking my first unknown book , the book of illusions attracted me. I chose it sensationally( I hadn&apos;t heared the name). Now, it&apos;s 2AM and i am pretty glad and satisfied of fi</span>
  <span id="freeText12088657711377576553" style="display:none">Usually, Im not used to experience reading a book without any previous suggestion. I often choose them with regard to their reputation; but that day, I was too tired of walking along the streets, performing my university chores till 1 PM. I wonder how a bookstore just appeared in front of me and I was attracted to its yard.picking my first unknown book , the book of illusions attracted me. I chose it sensationally( I hadn't heared the name). Now, it's 2AM and i am pretty glad and satisfied of finishing this book right now. Sometimes I wonder whether it's the writer who is so powerful or It's me that is suffering from lack of mental imaginations? Such skillfull creations and such unique descriptions that takes you to the atmosphere and helps you feel almost everything and such misguidings and deceives can only originate from a very creative mind. This book made me appraise him and I will definitely follow Paul Auster's works. :)<br /><br />معمولا عادت ندارم كتابي رو خودم تجربه كنم. هميشه طبق تعريف ديگران وشهرت، كتاب ها رو انتخاب ميكنم. اما اون روز اونقدر خسته بودم و تاساعت يك بعد از ظهر در خيابان ها دنبال كارهام بودم كه نميدونم چطور يه كتابفروشي گمنام جلوم سبز شد و من جذب فضاي حياطش شدم. باورم نميشه چطور تا ساعت سه و نيم توي اون كتابفروشي پرسه ميزدم و اولين بار تصميم گرفتم كتاب معروفي نخرم( حداقل تا اون موقع اسمشو نشنيده بودم). الان ساعت دو شبه و از اينكه همين الان اولين كتاب برگزيده ي حسي ام رو تموم كردم خيلي خوشحال و راضي ام. گاهي آدم با خودش فكر ميكنه اين نويسنده هست كه خيلي تواناست يا اين منم كه قدرت ذهني پاييني دارم؟ خلق داستان هايي با اين مهارت و همچين توصيف هاي نابي كه مو به مو فضا رو ميتوني لمس كني و اين همه به غلط انداختن و به قولي دست انداختن خواننده تنها از يه ذهن فوق خلاق بر مياد. اين كتاب تحسين من رو برانگيخت و باعث ميشه حتما كارهاي پل آستر رو دنبال كنم. هرچند از اينكه صحنه هايي از داستان، وقتي توي عمق داستان غرق شدي، ميبيني كه سانسور شدن خيلي خيلي عصبانيم ميكرد و به دفعات به خودم لعنت فرستادم كه چرا دارم با خوندن ترجمه، كل اثر رو نابود ميكنم واسه خودم.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12088657711377576553" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

